# ================================================================
# Systems Feature Prediction Ladder
# MMMSociability
# ================================================================
# Goal:
#   Extend 09_early_prediction_model_ladder.R with biologically grouped
#   systems-neuroscience features while keeping the manuscript-facing claim
#   conservative and reviewer-safe.
#
# Core logic:
#   1. Start from the validated 08b first-active-phase prediction table.
#   2. Optionally merge animal-level features generated by downstream scripts.
#   3. Build domain-wise feature sets:
#        - movement-derived RFID locomotor / trajectory
#        - temporal organization
#        - social organization
#        - rest / circadian architecture
#        - state / nonlinear dynamics
#   4. Compare a model ladder against raw movement-only prediction.
#   5. Use leave-one-animal-out prediction for all models.
#   6. Use elastic net when glmnet is available; otherwise fall back to lm.
#   7. Treat nonlinear models as exploratory sensitivity analyses only.
#
# Scientific framing:
#   This script should not replace 08b. Use 08b as the conservative primary
#   analysis. Use 08c to ask whether broader systems-level behavioral domains
#   improve prospective prediction of later CombZ beyond raw movement and the
#   compact Movement/Entropy/Proximity ladder.
#
# Important leakage rule:
#   Behavior-only models are the clean primary prediction models and exclude
#   both Sex and Group. Behavior + Sex models are sensitivity analyses testing
#   whether early behavior predicts later CombZ after sex adjustment. Behavior
#   + Sex + Group models are descriptive/group-informed upper bounds because
#   Group is related to later stress phenotyping and may encode outcome
#   structure.
# ================================================================

